data.chText: 到新地方
data.enText: to new place

data.chText: （使）转移，搬迁
data.enText: to move from one place to another; to move sth/sb from one place to another

data.chText: 这家电影制片厂正迁往好莱坞。
data.enText: The film studio is transferring to Hollywood.

data.chText: 怎么才能把我账户上的钱转到他的账户上呢？
data.enText: How can I transfer money from my bank account to his?

data.chText: 患者转送到了另一家医院。
data.enText: The patient was transferred to another hospital.

data.chText: 我无法把我在专科学校的所有学分都转过来。
data.enText: I couldn't transfer all my credits from junior college.

data.chText: 如果我在马德里上一学期的课，我的学分能转过来吗？
data.enText: If I spend a semester in Madrid, will my credits transfer?

data.chText: 到新的工作 / 学校 / 环境
data.enText: to new job/school/situation

data.chText: （使）调动；转职；转学；改变（环境）
data.enText: to move from one job, school, situation, etc. to another; to arrange for sb to move

data.chText: 儿童通常在11或12岁时升读中学。
data.enText: Children usually transfer to secondary school at 11 or 12.

data.chText: 他读完大学一年级后，转学到加利福尼亚大学洛杉矶分校。
data.enText: He transferred to UCLA after his freshman year.

data.chText: 十名雇员已调离销售部。
data.enText: Ten employees are being transferred from the sales department.

data.chText: 感觉；疾病；权力
data.enText: feeling/disease/power

data.chText: 转移（感情）；传染（疾病）；让与，转让（权力等）
data.enText: if you transfer a feeling, a disease, or power, etc., or if it transfers from one person to another, the second person has it, often instead of the first

data.chText: 乔已移情别恋，把爱意从莉萨转移到了克利奥身上。
data.enText: Joe had already transferred his affections from Lisa to Cleo.

data.chText: 这种疾病很少由母亲传给婴儿。
data.enText: This disease is rarely transferred from mother to baby (= so that the baby has it as well as the mother) .

data.chText: 财产
data.enText: property

data.chText: 转让；让与
data.enText: to officially arrange for sth to belong to sb else or for sb else to control sth

data.chText: 他把财产转让给了儿子。
data.enText: He transferred the property to his son.

data.chText: 体育运动
data.enText: in sport

data.chText: 转会，使转会（尤指职业足球队）
data.enText: to move, or to move sb, to a different sports team, especially a professional football ( soccer ) team

data.chText: 他以600万英镑的转会费转到埃弗顿队。
data.enText: He transferred to Everton for £6 million.

data.chText: 他以巨额转会费从热刺队转到阿森纳队。
data.enText: He was transferred from Spurs to Arsenal for a huge fee.

data.chText: 换乘交通工具
data.enText: to new vehicle

data.chText: （使在旅途中）转乘，换乘，倒车
data.enText: to change to a different vehicle during a journey; to arrange for sb to change to a different vehicle during a journey

data.chText: 我在巴林转乘飞往新加坡的班机。
data.enText: I transferred at Bahrain for a flight to Singapore.

data.chText: 旅客自机场改乘出租汽车到旅馆。
data.enText: Passengers are transferred from the airport to the hotel by taxi.

data.chText: 信息、音乐等
data.enText: information/music, etc.

data.chText: 转存，转录（资料、音乐等）；改编
data.enText: to copy information, music, an idea, etc. from one method of recording or presenting it to another; to be recorded or presented in a different way

data.chText: 你可以在几秒钟内将数据转存到磁盘上。
data.enText: You can transfer data to a disk in a few seconds.

data.chText: 这部小说不太适宜改编成电影。
data.enText: The novel does not transfer well to the movies.

data.chText: 地点 / 工作 / 环境的改变
data.enText: change of place/job/situation

data.chText: 搬迁；转移；调动；变换
data.enText: the act of moving sb/sth from one place, group or job to another; an occasion when this happens

data.chText: 电子数据传输
data.enText: electronic data transfer

data.chText: 货币从一国到另一国的汇划
data.enText: the transfer of currency from one country to another

data.chText: 他要求调到公司的巴黎分部。
data.enText: He has asked for a transfer to the company's Paris branch.

data.chText: 大选之后权力迅速交接。
data.enText: After the election there was a swift transfer of power .

data.chText: 体育运动
data.enText: in sport

data.chText: （运动员）转会
data.enText: the act of moving a sports player from one club or team to another

data.chText: 这是他从切尔西队转会过来之后的第一记入球。
data.enText: It was the first goal he had scored since his transfer from Chelsea.

data.chText: 转会费
data.enText: a transfer fee

data.chText: 上转会名单
data.enText: to be on the transfer list (= available to join another club)

data.chText: 转车
data.enText: change of vehicle

data.chText: （旅途中的）中转，换乘，改变路线
data.enText: an act of changing to a different place, vehicle or route when you are travelling

data.chText: 票价包括从机场转车到旅馆的费用。
data.enText: The transfer from the airport to the hotel is included in the price.

data.chText: 火车 / 公共汽车票
data.enText: train/bus ticket

data.chText: 转车票；换乘票
data.enText: a ticket that allows a passenger to continue their journey on another bus or train

data.chText: 图画
data.enText: picture
decal

data.chText: 转印图画，转印图案（利用挤压或加热，可从纸上转印到物体的表面）
data.enText: a picture or design that can be removed from a piece of paper and stuck onto a surface, for example by being pressed or heated

data.chText: 心理学
data.enText: psychology

data.chText: 迁移（将已习得的行为在新的情况下应用）
data.enText: the process of using behaviour which has already been learned in one situation in a new situation

simple_means.memory_skill: trans 转移 + fer 带来，拿来 → 转送；转移

tr: the act of transfering something from one form to another
example: the transfer of the music from record to tape suppressed much of the background noise

tr: the act of moving something from one location to another
application of a skill learned in one situation to a different but similar situation
a ticket that allows a passenger to change conveyances
someone who transfers or is transferred from one position to another
example: the best student was a transfer from LSU

tr: transfer from one place or period to another
example: The ancient Greek story was transplanted into Modern America

tr: send from one person or place to another
lift and reset in another soil or situation

example: transfer the packet from his trouser pockets to a pocket in his jacket

tr: shift the position or location of, as for business, legal, educational, or military purposes
example: He removed his children to the countryside
Remove the troops to the forest surrounding the city
remove a case to another court

tr: change from one vehicle or transportation line to another
example: She changed in Chicago on her way to the East coast
I transferred my stock holdings to my children

tr: move from one place to another
example: transfer the patient to another hospital

tr: transfer somebody to a different position or location of work

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /træns'fɜː/. The noun is pronounced /'trænsfɜː/. 动词读作 /træns'fɜː/。名词读作 /'trænsfɜː/。

value.def: If you transfer something or someone from one place to another, or they transfer from one place to another, they go from the first place to the second.

example.ex: Remove the wafers with a spoon and transfer them to a plate...
example.tran: 用勺子抄起薄饼，把它们转盛到盘子里。

example.ex: He was transferred from Weston Hospital to Frenchay…
example.tran: 他从韦斯顿医院转院到了法兰查。

example.ex: He wants to transfer some money to the account of his daughter…
example.tran: 他想把一些钱转到女儿的账户上。

example.ex: The person can transfer from wheelchair to seat with relative ease.
example.tran: 那个人可以比较轻松地从轮椅上移到座位上。

example.ex: Arrange for the transfer of medical records to your new doctor...
example.tran: 安排一下把病历转给你的新医生的事宜。

example.ex: The bank reserves the right to reverse any transfers or payments.
example.tran: 银行保留撤销任何转账或支付操作的权利。

value.def: If something is transferred, or transfers ,from one person or group of people to another, the second person or group gets it instead of the first.

example.ex: I realized she'd transferred all her love from me to you...
example.tran: 我意识到她已把所有的爱从我身上转移到了你身上。

example.ex: The chances of the disease being transferred to humans is extremely remote…
example.tran: 该疾病传播到人类身上的几率微乎其微。

example.ex: On 1 December the presidency of the Security Council automatically transfers from the US to Yemen.
example.tran: 12 月 1 日，联合国安全理事会的轮值主席国职位自动地由美国移交给也门。

example.ex: ...the transfer of power from the old to the new regimes.
example.tran: 新旧政权的权力移交

value.def: Technology transfer is the process or act by which a country or organization which has developed new technology enables another country or organization to use the technology.

example.ex: The Philippines needs capital and technology transfer...
example.tran: 菲律宾需要资本与技术转让。

example.ex: There will be a transfer of technology from this country to Mongolia.
example.tran: 这个国家将会向蒙古国进行技术转让。

value.def: In professional sports, if a player transfers or is transferred from one club to another, they leave one club and begin playing for another.

example.ex: ...Nick Barmby who transferred from Spurs to Middlesbrough...
example.tran: 从热刺队转会到米德尔斯伯勒队的尼克·巴尔姆比

example.ex: He was transferred from Crystal Palace to Arsenal for £2.5 million.
example.tran: 他以 250 万英镑的身价从水晶宫队转入阿森纳队。

example.ex: ...Gascoigne's transfer to the Italian club, Lazio.
example.tran: 加斯科因转会到意大利俱乐部拉齐奥

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 trade

value.def: If you are transferred, or if you transfer ,to a different job or place, you move to a different job or start working in a different place.

example.ex: I was transferred to the book department...
example.tran: 我被调到图书部。

example.ex: I suspect that she is going to be transferred...
example.tran: 我猜想她要被调走了。

example.ex: Anton was able to transfer from Lavine's to an American company.
example.tran: 安东成功地从拉文调到了一家美国公司。

example.ex: They will be offered transfers to other locations.
example.tran: 他们将会被安排调任到其他地方。

gramarinfo.label: Also V n, V n <l>from/to</l> n

value.def: When information is transferred onto a different medium, it is copied from one medium to another.

example.ex: Such information is easily transferred onto microfilm.
example.tran: 这种信息很容易转存到缩微胶卷上。

example.ex: ...systems to create film-quality computer effects and then transfer them to film.
example.tran: 创造胶片级电脑画质并将之转录到胶片的系统

example.ex: It can be connected to a PC for the transfer of information.
example.tran: 它可以与个人电脑连接进行信息转存。

example.ex: ...data transfer.
example.tran: 数据转存

value.def: When property or land is transferred, it stops being owned by one person or institution and becomes owned by another.

example.ex: He has already transferred ownership of most of the works to a British foundation...
example.tran: 他已把大部分作品的所有权转让给一家英国基金会。

example.ex: Certain kinds of property are transferred automatically at death.
example.tran: 死亡时某些财产会自动转让。

example.ex: ...an outright transfer of property.
example.tran: 财产的全部让与

value.def: If you transfer or are transferred when you are on a journey, you change from one vehicle to another.

example.ex: He likes to transfer from the bus to the Blue Line at 103rd Street in Watts...
example.tran: 他喜欢在华兹区第 103 大街下公交车转乘地铁蓝线。

example.ex: 1,654 passengers were transferred at sea to a Norwegian cruise ship.
example.tran: 1,654 名乘客在海上转搭了一艘挪威游轮。

value.def: Transfers are pieces of paper with a design on one side. The design can be transferred by heat or pressure onto material, paper, or china for decoration.

example.ex: ...gold letter transfers.
example.tran: 金字转印纸

value.tran: 转印纸(纸上面印有图案，可通过加热或压力转印至其他材料上)

value.def: A transfer is a ticket that you get when you leave a bus or train that allows you to go on a different bus or train without paying again.
